@page
@model SE_Project.Pages.ViewFYPModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "View FYP";
}

<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <div class="text-center mb-5">
                <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold"><i class="bi bi-file-earmark-text-fill text-primary"></i> Your FYP Details</h1>
                <hr class="my-4">
            </div>
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-person-fill text-secondary"></i> Supervisor</h3>
                    <p class="card-text fw-bold">Arshad Islam</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-journal-text-fill text-secondary"></i> Project Name</h3>
                    <p class="card-text fw-bold">Kumon</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill text-secondary"></i> Details</h3>
                    <p class="card-text fw-bold">
                        To convey the essence and significance of my project idea, I would emphasize its core objective of fortifying network security within Kubernetes environments using cutting-edge technologies. By integrating eBPF, Cilium, and other observability tools, the project aims to create a robust defense mechanism against a myriad of potential threats, ranging from traditional attacks like DDoS and packet spoofing to modern challenges such as cache poisoning and container runtime vulnerabilities. This initiative is not merely about mitigating risks; it represents a proactive approach towards safeguarding critical infrastructure and sensitive data in an era where containerized applications and microservices architectures are ubiquitous. Through comprehensive security measures, including intrusion detection, encryption, vulnerability management, and incident response capabilities, the project endeavors to instill confidence in Kubernetes administrators and developers, assuring them of a resilient and secure platform for deploying and managing mission-critical workloads. Ultimately, this project serves as a testament to the commitment towards advancing the state-of-the-art in Kubernetes security, fostering a culture of continuous improvement and vigilance in the face of evolving cyber threats.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill text-secondary"></i> Feedbacks</h3>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p class="card-text fw-bold">
                                Great work
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p class="card-text fw-bold">
                                Well done
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                   
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<script>
    // Read username from localStorage
    var username = localStorage.getItem('username');
    // Set the value of the hidden input field
    document.getElementById('username').value = username;
</script>
